('Product2', 'SubProductI', 100000),
('Product3', 'SubProductK', 400),
('Product3', 'SubProductL', 500)
```

What we need is a query which will place the product with the highest individual value at the top, followed by the sub-product with the highest value at the top, with all product / sub-product groups being kept together.

We would like to end up with a table like the one below, where:

- Product 2 comes first, since it contains the highest individual sales amount, followed by product 1 and then product 3. All elements of Product 2 are kept together at the top of the table, even though some items for Product 2 have a lower value than those of other products.
- SubProduct G comes first since it contains the highest sales amount. Again the two SubProductG records are kept together even though the second row has a lower value than some other sub-products - we want to maintain the grouping.

